headline: Regulators scold Union Pacific for lack of cooperation
summary: The Surface Transportation Board has taken Union Pacific to task for an ongoing lack of cooperation in a new decision on the railroad’s effort to construct a 6-mile rail line in Arizona’s Maricopa and Pinal counties. The post Regulators scold Union Pacific for lack of cooperation appeared first on FreightWaves.
